[% INCLUDE section label="Zooming" %]

[% WRAPPER html/todo %]
Document zooming correctly.
[% END %]

[% FILTER html_para %]
You can zoom in on any part of plot by selecting
[% INCLUDE font/quote a="Zoom" %] from the
Plot menu or by typing
[% INCLUDE modkey key="control" letter='=' %].  You will be prompted
in the echo area to click on two points in the plot.  Those two points
are the corners of a box surrounding the part of the plot you want to
zoom in to.  You can zoom repeatedly.  Selecting
[% INCLUDE font/quote a="Unzoom" %] from the Plot menu or typing
[% INCLUDE modkey key="control" letter='-' %] will restore the
original plot.  Incremental unzooming is not implemented.
[% END %]

